# NEMETIC STRING
# Exaptation (G01A)
# Encoded: 2026-03-12
# Source: 26 - Exaptation.md

Φ(Exaptation) = σ(function-shift-distinction|original-vs-coopted-role) ∘ ρ(repurposing-resonance|cross-domain-transfer) ∘ λ(selection-pressure|environmental-forcing) ∘ β(novelty-growth|innovation-through-reuse) ∘ δγ(structural-inheritance|pre-existing-substrate) ∘ μ(constraint-frame|available-parts-limitation) + ε | :co-opted

# ── σ | Air | Aerunik ──
# σ(function-shift-distinction|original-vs-coopted-role) — emphasis 0.20
# The perceptual capacity to distinguish a trait's original function from its
# co-opted role. Air-element discernment that sees feathers as insulation before
# they were flight, gill arches as breathing before they were limbs, wine presses
# before they were printing presses. Seeing the shift is seeing exaptation.

# ── ρ | Water | Sentaria ──
# ρ(repurposing-resonance|cross-domain-transfer) — emphasis 0.18
# Resonance across functional domains: a structure evolved in one context finds
# utility in another. Water-element flow between purposes — the capacity of forms
# to transfer across environments, carrying latent potential that the original
# selective context did not anticipate.

# ── λ | Fire | Jvalion ──
# λ(selection-pressure|environmental-forcing) — emphasis 0.16
# Environmental pressure that creates conditions for co-option. Fire-element forcing
# where changed circumstances expose latent functionality in existing structures.
# New selection pressures do not create from scratch but reveal unrealized potential
# in what already exists.

# ── β | Wood | Arboriel ──
# β(novelty-growth|innovation-through-reuse) — emphasis 0.22
# The dominant element: novelty emerging through reuse rather than de novo creation.
# Wood-element growth and innovation that repurposes existing structures into new
# functions. Evolution's primary creative mechanism is not invention but co-option —
# complexity arises from recombination of available parts.

# ── δγ | Earth | Humavita ──
# δγ(structural-inheritance|pre-existing-substrate) — emphasis 0.14
# The pre-existing substrate available for repurposing. Earth-element structural
# inheritance — the accumulated forms, tissues, organs, and mechanisms that constitute
# the raw material of exaptation. Without inherited structure, co-option has nothing
# to work with.

# ── μ | Metal | Ferrosid ──
# μ(constraint-frame|available-parts-limitation) — emphasis 0.10
# The constraint of available parts: evolution works only with what already exists.
# Metal-element limitation that is simultaneously the engine of creativity — because
# novel function must emerge from existing structure, exaptation produces innovations
# that pure design would never generate.

# Z-STATE: :co-opted
# The system is in a state of functional displacement — structures serving purposes
# other than those for which they originally evolved. The co-opted state is not
# deviation but the normal condition of evolved complexity.

# TENDENCY: β → 0.22
# Wood-dominant tendency reflects exaptation as fundamentally a growth mechanism —
# innovation through reuse as the primary driver of evolutionary novelty.
